Adding MIT license to the gemspec.

Merge pull request #2 from bkabrda/patch-1

Fix specs for Ruby 2.0.0

Update little-plugger_spec.rb

On Ruby 2.0.0, NameError contains only the last part of constant name (e.g. "Plugins" in this case).
ensure the order of the returned gemspecs
updating to latest version of rspec
Resovling a circular dependency with Mr Bones.
Adding a rubyforge name so I can still release to rubyforge.

Catching more errors when loading.

I don't want a poopy plugin (or an incompatible version) to crash the current
application when plugins are loaded. Rescuing a few more errors and skipping
the bad plugins.
Adding the option to disregard plugins by name.

Loading the first found plugin.

Previously, the if there were two plugins using the same name the last one
found was the one that was loaded. This behaviour has been changed such that
the first plugin found is the one that is loaded.

The Gem#find_files method searches the load path first and then gems sorted by
their names / version numbers. Load the first found plugin favors the load
path and newer gem releases.
If there are now plugin names specified, then all plugins that are found will be loaded.
